Package: pqlite3
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Post-Quantum SQLite - command-line interface
 PQLite is a fork of SQLite that adds NIST-standardized post-quantum
 cryptographic (PQC) protection. Features ML-KEM key encapsulation
 (FIPS 203), AES-256-GCM page encryption, ML-DSA digital signatures
 (FIPS 204), column-level encryption, cryptographic audit logging,
 and FIPS 140-3 compliance mode.
 .
 This package contains the pqlite3 command-line shell.
 .
 PQLite is a product of Dyber, Inc.

Package: libpqlite3-0
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Post-Quantum SQLite - shared library
 PQLite is a fork of SQLite that adds NIST-standardized post-quantum
 cryptographic (PQC) protection using ML-KEM (FIPS 203), ML-DSA
 (FIPS 204), and AES-256-GCM encryption.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libpqlite3-dev
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Section: libdevel
Depends: libpqlite3-0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Post-Quantum SQLite - development files
 PQLite is a fork of SQLite that adds NIST-standardized post-quantum
 cryptographic (PQC) protection.
 .
 This package contains the header files and static library for
 developing applications that use PQLite.
